messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path: /api/articles

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: true

- POST: false

- OPTIONS: true

- TRACE: false

- GET: true

- PUT: false

- DELETE: false

- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- ArticleList is registered under the anonymous articles routes with router.GET("/", ArticleList). This means the endpoint responds to GET requests at the articles group path. The group path is typically mounted as /api/articles in the main router (i.e., a versioned API prefix plus an articles sub-group), giving the full path /api/articles. There are no dynamic path parameters for ArticleList, so no curly-braced placeholders are needed.
- Since only GET is explicitly registered for this route, not all methods are acceptable.
- In Gin, HEAD is typically handled automatically for routes that have a GET handler, so HEAD is effectively acceptable.
- OPTIONS is usually handled automatically by the router to advertise allowed methods for existing routes, so OPTIONS is acceptable as well.
- All other methods (POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH, TRACE) are not defined for this endpoint, so they are not acceptable here.
